file raw frames to include lines, but I'm not sure if that would be allowed. The limitation seems to be around having the source context. Could I generate a dynamic coverage report that falls back to method coverage instead?\nhuman-intervention-logs/commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-05T03-37-40-001855Z.log:5766:[thinking] **Considering coverage reporting**\nhuman-intervention-logs/commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-05T03-37-40-001855Z.log:5768:[thinking] I'm thinking about whether I could provide debug info by replacing a dependency with a recompiled jar from source, but that might not be allowed. Maybe I could use a patched class for testing, but it feels like I'm hitting a wall there. The external report isn’t marking newly covered methods because it requires line coverage. While the task focuses on tests, I wonder if I can implement a line info mapping fallback in the report generator. But there are restrictions about broadening patches into unrelated features.\nhuman-intervention-logs/commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-05T03-37-40-001855Z.log:5770:[thinking] **Improving dynamic coverage**\nhuman-intervention-logs/commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-05T03-37-40-001855Z.log:5772:[thinking] I'm considering how we could enhance dynamic coverage infrastructure to implement a method coverage fallback for frames without lines. However, the developer only wants to add or refine tests, focusing on the active class. It seems modifying Jacoco XML or using a public API for reflection might not be feasible. The dynamic-access report's call sites are in library classes, but coverage shows as \"covered\" if the line number is null. The challenge lies in the library jar not having line tables, so including a source jar with debug info might be a potential solution.\nhuman-intervention-logs/commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-05T03-37-40-001855Z.log:5776:[tool-call] delta {\"command\":\"javap -classpath ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/commons-collections/commons-collections/2.0/abf9656768db720f93eae5b6db079c7ca6bcf811/commons-collections-2.0.jar -l org.apache.commons.collections.BeanMap | head -100\"}\nhuman-intervention-logs/commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-05T03-37-40-001855Z.log:5777:[tool-call] end id=call_VbOdce6hW8on3fgUsMBGY3ZR|fc_0602a48bffbeae510169f966a3f1748196bf07c3d87eb44041 name=bash args={\"command\": \"javap -classpath ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/commons-collections/commons-collections/2.0/abf9656768db720f93eae5b6db079c7ca6bcf811/commons-collections-2.0.jar -l org.apache.commons.collections.BeanMap | head -100\"}\nhuman-intervention-logs/commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-05T03-37-40-001855Z.log:5778:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Exploring coverage challenges**\\n\\nI'm looking at Jacoco method coverage and realizing that the dynamic report only shows line coverage. If there's no line, it can't mark it. How can I improve coverage? I might think of altering the build to change the dynamic access file raw frames to include lines, but I'm not sure if that would be allowed. The limitation seems to be around having the source context. Could I generate a dynamic coverage report that falls back to method coverage instead?\\n\\n**Considering coverage reporting**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether I could provide debug info by replacing a dependency with a recompiled jar from source, but that might not be allowed. Maybe I could use a patched class for testing, but it feels like I'm hitting a wall there. The external report isn’t marking newly covered methods because it requires line coverage. While the task focuses on tests, I wonder if I can implement a line info mapping fallback in the report generator. But there are restrictions about broadening patches into unrelated features.\\n\\n**Improving dynamic coverage**\\n\\nI'm considering how we could enhance dynamic coverage infrastructure to implement a method coverage fallback for frames without lines. However, the developer only wants to add or refine tests, focusing on the active class. It seems modifying Jacoco XML or using a public API for reflection might not be feasible. The dynamic-access report's call sites are in library classes, but coverage shows as \\\"covered\\\" if the line number is null. The challenge lies in the library jar not having line tables, so including a source jar with debug info might be a potential solution.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0602a48bffbeae510169f9669a6df48196bfcd6160591dcf0e\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-WajdxKKPAqu2Y0Wj5rdXkWJGzaO6H9FrbbTrBQ64zaPR8KEpJb949C2gSe5_LmHwot1kGVX3p38oEGUGYcv5URNptENLBW9o-tFsvg9vyvsKpaeEg9FDD6nha019kGbmsTa-Bc9uGmG2b0id4SGrsBwhtTAKR_18G8MiVpLz7ls8TjH4jJTOqOUDcJCnMI69INSO7nMqu-gttx1SE9yi9XKHDUuv-AvywLgCxkG0O2R233K328WSXLGhQXVOOHr3J_tA4d9mcWDF44n1Fpk2XlfjtwceOuQv20Fdg18Nl1A321eX66bNGMbZ4B6d4Nk0lONm0UkiiFdOhvj789dkJHPukZEicPszytt65UtK7TgvypOccDoHYDoCLsDiC2cZKw4FyFiYOE0Ipr1EoZ4n_jPhjNvHnJRp9hav6qsOFczO7dTRzcirAePl2K8UTEqCIkpAD8mkijpyqH_d2l5BaGQ7CPRCyMJtUEHhSUCNx5pan7I75BaXqGBZPvTLs2Hnsp-BwbbTmsXfR-BZvpj2JqHZDjqKA_W4g63tkw1KtV5VIAiUbkvNl22kbW32dfksL_SttBpCOf98iSU4qIRJHWTPucmkIh2eMQZh-HfNJjAoIrNHLD-vgsPu5I7D-D-7NL5XWG8TDPCbV5xKEfH-6AMESVLHqRTCER0Vg_GlYclEOBdNTHMzFspyEan_DMAt8061srR0BgsqH8LU7gXxC3hZ99MNblR3FGrgTx9eSZkML9TDP3-GabIBQlOHwQitOMQo_jir5PK8f42ZIDs6pbifaaXkVALblOk4uPrqPF-sK_wa3535lDiCHFE5W6_OOhUi_FvM1T-2Vb8HV6L6wuAZvMpW8Ou8sfBYH2wfuoP6QAK9bgztBY7Q872Mc5os65geAjlVyQBFbaut1-BpTCjr8A-PcAo2L6qDjTt90-vf7o7oE0j3lsSk2GIqTi-W2_6N5QQG